    "15981984": {
      "title": "On the dimension of a graph",
      "abstract": "Our purpose in this note is to present a natural geometrical definition of the dimension of a graph and to explore some of its ramifications. In $1 we determine the dimension of some special graphs. We observe in 92 that several results in the literature are unified by the concept of the dimension of a graph, and state some related unsolved problems. We define the dimension of a graph G, denoted dim G, as the minimum number n such that G can be embedded into Euclidean n-space E,, with every edge of G having length 1. The vertices of C are mapped onto distinct points of E,, but there is no restriction on the crossing of edges."
